Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest and cut the @Lime{1} into wedges.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways.

Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Lay the @Salmon Fillets{2}(skin-side down) onto one side of a lined #baking tray{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle over the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}.

Pop the Tenderstem® broccoli onto the other half of the baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the salmon and broccoli on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once the rice is cooked, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic. Stir fry for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @Orkney Crab Meat{100%g}. Fry for ~{1%min}.

Add the cooked rice, @Peas{120%g}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml} and @Sambal Paste{15%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir well to combine. Fry, stirring frequently, until piping hot, ~{2-3%mins}.

Once the salmon is cooked, drizzle over the @Honey{1%tbsp}.

When everything's ready, stir the lime zest and a squeeze of lime juice into the rice.

Share your spiced salmon, crab nasi goreng and broccoli between your plates in separate sections.

Squeeze a little lime juice over the broccoli. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

Sprinkle the peanuts over the top of everything to finish.

Enjoy!